Some tech time! Rebuilding my Classic Army M249 mkII. Bought seconhand with broken internals. But when opening it I found a A&K box and parts not matching eachother.... for example a bigbore cyl with a standard size alu pistonhead facing a non rubberized cyl head? Wtf!... no wonder the thing broke down. / Klockar -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Parts list ( so far):
◾new CA gearbox
◾CA piston
◾CA stock gear set I had laying
◾SHS sector gear delay clip
◾ASG Ultimate CNC motor ◾ASG Ultimate cylinder
◾ASG Ultimate cylinder head
◾ASG Ultimate nozzle ◾ASG Ultimate alu piston head
◾ASG Ultimate anti reverse latch
◾ASG Ultimate 8mm ball bearings
◾should I invest in one of those fancy hop up units for this one? Is it worth it? -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
